reviews.text: Love the food, especially the 避风塘螃蟹. It’s damn pricey though. Other favorites include the braised goose and the 东风螺.

Authentic Chinese Chiu Chow restaurant. The owner is a hardworking old Chinese man who works with his two sons, they are very welcoming and aimed to give me an outstanding authentic Chinese restaurant experience.
Bring a wine. No corkage fee.
It was okay. Food was nothing spectacular but they were open during Typhoon Mangkhut so I give them that. Nice people too😀
Expensive and food is not good.
